    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Duplicate Bill Download Guide — All Pakistan Utilities 2026</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">Losing your utility bill is a common problem in Pakistan — printed bills arrive by post and can be delayed, misplaced, or simply never delivered. Whether it's your LESCO electricity bill, SNGPL gas bill, or WASA water bill, you don't need to wait for a replacement to be mailed. Every major utility in Pakistan now offers <strong>online duplicate bill download</strong> — a PDF version that's identical to the printed bill (same barcode, same account details, same amount, same due date) and is accepted at all banks, JazzCash, EasyPaisa, and 1Bill retailers. This guide covers the duplicate bill download process for every major utility in Pakistan.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Summary: Visit pakistanbill.online → select your utility checker → enter your reference number (electricity: 14-digit) or consumer number (gas/water: 8–10 digit) → click "Download PDF" to save the duplicate bill. Free, instant, no login required.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Duplicate Electricity Bill Download</h2>
