    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Is the Duplicate Bill Valid for Payment?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4"><strong>Yes — 100% valid.</strong> The PDF duplicate downloaded from pakistanbill.online is identical to the printed bill:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Same barcode (banks scan this for payment)</li>
      <li>Same account/consumer details</li>
      <li>Same bill amount</li>
      <li>Same due date</li>
      <li>Same reference/consumer number</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">All banks (HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, Bank Alfalah, Meezan, Faysal), mobile wallets (JazzCash, EasyPaisa), and 1Bill retailers accept the duplicate PDF for payment. If a bank teller refuses the duplicate (rare), request to speak to the branch manager — the duplicate is officially recognized by all DISCOs.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips for Downloading Duplicate Bills</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Save the reference number once.</strong> Store your 14-digit electricity reference number and 10-digit gas consumer number in your phone's notes — you'll never need to find an old bill again.</li>
      <li><strong>Download before the due date.</strong> Don't wait for the last day — bank servers may be busy near due dates and online bill checkers can be slow.</li>
      <li><strong>Print clearly</strong> if you're paying at a bank counter — faded printouts may not scan at the barcode reader.</li>
      <li><strong>Email yourself the PDF</strong> after downloading — serves as a backup if you lose the printout.</li>
      <li><strong>Check for typos before downloading.</strong> A single wrong digit in the reference number will return someone else's bill or "no bill found".</li>
      <li><strong>Use mobile data</strong> if home Wi-Fi is slow — the bill checkers are lightweight and load quickly even on 2G.</li>
    </ul>

