    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to download duplicate electricity bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit pakistanbill.online and select your DISCO (LESCO, K-Electric, IESCO, FESCO etc.). Enter your 14-digit reference number. Your current month's bill appears. Click 'Download PDF' to save a duplicate copy. The PDF is accepted at all banks and payment retailers.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to download duplicate gas bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">For SNGPL (Punjab/KP/AJK): Visit pakistanbill.online/sngpl-bill/ and enter your 10-digit consumer number. For SSGC (Sindh/Balochistan): Visit pakistanbill.online/ssgc-bill/ and enter your 10-digit consumer number. Click 'Download PDF' to save the duplicate.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is duplicate bill valid for payment?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. The PDF duplicate downloaded from pakistanbill.online is identical to the printed bill — it includes the same barcode, account details, amount, and due date. All banks, JazzCash, EasyPaisa, and 1Bill retailers accept the duplicate for payment.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to download duplicate WASA water bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Visit pakistanbill.online/wasa-lahore-bill/ (or /wasa-faisalabad-bill/ or /wasa-rawalpindi-bill/) and enter your 8-digit WASA consumer number. Click 'Download PDF' to save the duplicate water bill.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I download old bills from previous months?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Most DISCOs only show the current month's bill online. For previous month bills, contact your utility's customer service or visit their office. LESCO and K-Electric also offer billing history through their official customer portals.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Does downloading duplicate bill cost money?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">No. Duplicate bill download from pakistanbill.online is completely free. There are no fees, no subscriptions, no login required. We do not ask for your CNIC, bank details, or any sensitive information — only the utility reference/consumer number.</div></details>
